{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The article elaborates how these two literacies can be interwoven in a threestep process of awareness, reflection, and empowerment (Schmitt et al. 2018), and how their interrelation can be further developed into a model to create synergies empowering people to stand up against disinformation.",
    "In our Synergistic Literacy Model Against Disinformation, we argue that the individual literacies together contribute to the shaping of a comprehensive empowerment for living in a digitally driven culture by using media responsibly, critically examining media forms, exploring media effects, and finally deconstructing alternative media (Kellner and Share 2005).",
    "In the long run, to combat online disinformation, an examination of the interplay of media and data literacy competencies is crucial for educators, learners, and developers of media tools.",
    "We argue in a broader sense that such emerging sets of competencies -if they are encouraged by a digital infrastructure offering learning opportunities -facilitate participation in modern society (Marten 2010).",
    "Ultimately, they may stabilize democracy and thus contribute not only to digital literacy in general but also to civic literacy and participatory citizenship."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The article elaborates how these two literacies can be interwoven in a threestep process of awareness, reflection, and empowerment (Schmitt et al. 2018), and how their interrelation can be further developed into a model to create synergies empowering people to stand up against disinformation.",
    "In our Synergistic Literacy Model Against Disinformation, we argue that the individual literacies together contribute to the shaping of a comprehensive empowerment for living in a digitally driven culture by using media responsibly, critically examining media forms, exploring media effects, and finally deconstructing alternative media (Kellner and Share 2005).",
    "We argue in a broader sense that such emerging sets of competencies -if they are encouraged by a digital infrastructure offering learning opportunities -facilitate participation in modern society (Marten 2010)."
